\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\fs26 23. Final Summary\par
\b0\fs22 This Atlas project uses blockchain as an immutable event ledger for product movement. Each product gets a verifiable lifecycle. The backend reads that lifecycle and sends it to a fraud-analysis layer that checks whether the route and behavior match expected supply-chain behavior. Customers can verify authenticity, while Atlas can monitor suspicious activity.\par
\par
The core technical idea is simple: old records are not edited; new records are appended; suspicious patterns are detected from the full recorded history.\par
}
